ATTACHMENT A
Rate Schedule FERC No. 1 Settlers Trail Wind Farm, LLC Reactive Power Compensation January 12, 2018
SETTLERS TRAIL WIND FARM, LLC
RATE SCHEDULE FERC NO. 1
Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service
Settlers Trail Wind Farm, LLC ("Settlers Trail") provides Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service ("Reactive Supply Service") from the Settlers Trail generating facility ("Settlers Trail Facility").
The Settlers Trail Facility is a wind turbine generating facility located in Iroquois County, Illinois. The Settlers Trail Facility is interconnected to transmission facilities owned by Ameren Illinois Company and under the operational control of the Midcontinent Independent System Operator, Inc. ("MISO").
This Rate Schedule FERC No. 1 sets forth Settlers Trail's revenue requirement for Reactive Supply Service from the Settlers Trail Facility. This Rate Schedule shall be effective upon the date authorized by the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission.
Settlers Trail's monthly fixed revenue requirement consists of the charge for the Fixed Capability Component. Payment to Settlers Trail shall be subject to Schedule 2 of MISO's Open Access Transmission, Energy and Operating Reserve Markets Tariff.
MONTHLY REVENUE REQUIREMENT:
The Annual Reactive Service Revenue Requirement is: $552,000.00. The Monthly Reactive Service Revenue Requirement is: $46,000.00.
